        <abstract>
            <p>On geological works of Tschudi and Buch.</p>
            <p>"My health keeps indifferent &amp; I do not suppose I shall ever be a strong man again: everything fatigues me, &amp; I can work but little at my writing: this summer, however, I shall get out my geology of S. America".</p>
            <p>"I found Bronn’s Geschichte, which you recommended me, very useful, for references to facts on variation".</p>
